Vul detail
In the router module DDNS, user can setup DDNS(Dynamic Domain Name Server) with http post request. An normal request looks like below.

After setup DDNS, DDNS module will save data to config file.

If we send request with long value in specific json key, it will overflow and break the DDNS module config file.
If the string long enough it will also crash the inetd task, this will stop most network services, such as http, dns and upnp.

